The paper discusses the integration of privileged information into detection algorithms using machine learning techniques. This topic is closely related to computer security (cs.CR) as it aims to improve the accuracy of detection systems for identifying attacks. The paper also mentions the use of knowledge transfer, model influence, and distillation, which are common machine learning techniques used in areas such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and deep learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed approach in domains such as malware classification and facial user authentication, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.NE, in that order.
